attributes.description:
Purposes:
•	Generate materials about a work event that will be perceived as ambiguous in terms of overall event justice, using clear information on justice dimensions (but misaligned);
•	Validate a scale on justice ambiguity;
•	Validate scales that will be used as dependent variables in the follow-up study (organizational citizenship behaviors towards organization and towards supervisor and decision acceptance).

q2.value:
H1: Scenarios with misalignment in justice dimensions will be rated on justice ambiguity above the middle point of the justice ambiguity scale, while scenarios with alignment among justice dimensions will be rated on justice ambiguity below the middle point of the justice ambiguity scale;
H2: All scenarios will be rated above the middle point of the scale on justice clarity, by dimension;
H3: Justice ambiguity, justice clarity, overall event justice, organizational citizenship behaviors towards organization and towards supervisor and decision acceptance will have discriminant validity.

question.value:
We manipulate the ambiguity of justice of an event in an organizational context (a promotion decision) by combining, in each experimental condition – i.e., each scenario presented to the participants – fair/high vs. unfair/low information for each of three justice dimensions (distributive, procedural, and interactional). Thus, the following eight conditions were created: 
•	High distributive justice/ high procedural justice / high interactional justice;
•	High distributive justice/ high procedural justice / low interactional justice;
•	High distributive justice/ low procedural justice / high interactional justice; 
•	High distributive justice/ low procedural justice / low interactional justice; 
•	Low distributive justice/ low procedural justice / low interactional justice; 
•	Low distributive justice/ high procedural justice / high interactional justice; 
•	Low distributive justice/ high procedural justice / low interactional justice; 
•	Low distributive justice/ low procedural justice / high interactional justice. 
Please see the specific pieces of information that were manipulated and the resulting eight scenarios in the document attached.

